title: Fastest Cars in the Dirty South
subTitle: The 256 takes a young racer who is losing a lot this racing season and tries to turn him into a success at one of Alabama's biggest grudge race events. Eric, Malcolm and the team decide to mentor Jaleel Jackson, adjusting his car and his psyche.

subTitle: Kevin and the Boyz take their first educational field trip to the Irwindale Drag Strip, where they learn about power and engine boosts from experienced locals.

subTitle: A Lancia Fulvia coupe may be Drew and Paul most exciting project as they enter it into a prestigious concours event, but its problems could sabotage their ambitions.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike hopes to capitalise on 80s nostalgia by restoring an original 1982 Toyota Supra. Can Ant bring this car into the modern era without losing its originality?

subTitle: After an unfinished list shakeup, Ryan and Chief finally line up to race off for number one. With the list complete, the 405 gets ready for their first exciting list race of the season.

title: Kevin Hart's Muscle Car Crew
subTitle: Kevin Hart and his Plastic Cup Boyz want to make their passion for cars legit, but to do it, they need a serious education about cars and car culture.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike buys a 1995 Ford Escort RS Cosworth, a rare vehicle originally designed to qualify as a car for the World Rally Championship. Ant attempts to bring back the 227 hp engine's famous 'fizz' and adds a special detail.

subTitle: Chad Hiltz makes an elegant one-of-a-kind coupe in his shop. He uses spare parts, recycled metal and a rusted out 1939 Studebaker Commander to build the car.

subTitle: After a difficult end to last season's list racing, the 405 agree to a list shakeup: everyone loses his spot on the list and has to race to earn a new place.

subTitle: The Boyz take a trip to Radford Racing School in Arizona and learn driving techniques. Spank and Lucky talk engines, interiors, and paint, but the budget stands in the way of Spank's dreams.

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: The top three prep their cars to be ready for race night, and Farmtruck and AZN line up against Murder Nova's dad. On race night, tensions flare between Chuck and Shane, while racers questions each other when callouts are not made.
